Possibly related to CONFCLOUD-53510

h3. Issue Summary

When importing a Space with Templates from Confluence A to Confluence B, any mentions in the Templates will get broken, even if the usernames in the source and target instances are the same.

It seems related to CONFSERVER-34994. Templates use the *user_key* to make the reference to the target user, instead of the *username*.


h3. Steps to Reproduce
 # Create the same user (e.g. 'test.user') in Confluence A and Confluence B;
 # In Confluence A, create a Template with a mention 'test.user';
 # Export the space containing the template;
 # Import into Confluence B;
 # In Confluence B, create a page using the template imported;
 # Save the page and check the mention;

h3. Expected Results

We should see a proper mention to 'test.user';
h3. Actual Results

We see *Broken Link* or *Not an unresolved user* errors instead of the mention.

h3. Workaround

This KB contains a script to fix all the user_keys after the import:
 - [https://confluence.atlassian.com/confkb/user-mentions-appear-as-broken-link-after-xml-import-717062858.html]

