h3. Issue Summary

Confluence's '[Assign Space Permissions|https://confluence.atlassian.com/doc/assign-space-permissions-139460.html]' documentation explains how to manage and recover space admin permissions as below:
{panel}
h2. Manage and recover space admin permissions

If you're a Confluence Administrator you can recover permissions to a space, for example if the only person with Space Admin permissions to a space leaves your organisation.

*To recover Space Admin permissions:*
 # Go to    !https://confluence.atlassian.com/doc/files/747833194/747833195/2/1517274813281/cog.png|width=16!  > *General Configuration* > *Space Permissions*.
 # Locate the space in the Individual Spaces list and choose *Recover Permissions*.

You can then choose *Manage Permissions*, and add any other appropriate permissions to the space. Requests to recover permissions are recorded in the Confluence audit log.  

{color:#ff0000}Users with System Administrator permissions are able to manage permissions for all spaces, they do not need to first recover permissions.{color}
{panel}
The paragraph highlighted in red above states an inaccurate information.  

In order to be able to *Manage Permissions* for all spaces without needing to first *Recover Permissions*, users need to be members of the *confluence-administrator* group. If an user only has *System Administrator* permissions, it is still necessary to first recover permissions of a space
h3. How to Improve

Change the paragraph from:
{panel}
Users with System Administrator permissions are able to manage permissions for all spaces, they do not need to first recover permissions.
{panel}
To:
{panel}
Users members of the confluence-administrator group are able to manage permissions for all spaces, they do not need to first recover permissions.
{panel}

h3. Issue Summary
Admin functionality that allows them to either update user's profile picture using REST API. Currently, users are only able to use the GET methods for *user* data. 


h3. Expected Results
PUT /rest/user/<user ID or  name>
h3. Actual Results
only GET /rest/user is available. 


{code:java}
http://localhost:8090/rest/api/user?username=candacestark
{code}


